      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
         <p>The Executive Papers of Governor Westmoreland Davis are housed in 52 boxes. The collection is arranged alphabetically by topic with clemency and appointment materials filed at the end. These records include applications, appointments, correspondence, extraditions, invitations, pardons, reports, and requisitions. These records document the gubernatorial administration of Westmoreland Davis, 1 February 1918 to 1 February 1922.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
         <p>The General Correspondence are arranged alphabetically by topic. Subjects include: Adjutant General, Attorney General, Capitol Building and Grounds, Elections, Game and Inland Fisheries, General Assembly, Judges, Labor, Lime Grinding Plant, Penitentiary, Railroads, Roads, Schools, Virginia War History Commission, War Correspondence, George Washington (Houdon Statue), and Extraditions, Pardons, and Appointments.</p>
      </scopecontent>
